continueAttack = False
fdiainject()[fuente]

Injects messages into a topic chosen by the user.

This function injects messagges into one topic, decided by the user who invokes the node However, this function is no portable. It will send always the same type of message: geometry_msgs/PoseStamped Message

DataExample:

The following is an example of the message data sent by this function:

header:
    stamp:
        sec: 1731787676
        nanosec: 314306003
    frame_id: map
pose:
    position:
        x: 0.815548477931251
        y: -0.7515952102717546
        z: 0.6082673520391061
    orientation:
        x: -0.0006039200934903616
        y: 0.0009935296803737891
        z: 0.0011008786532515124
        w: 0.9999987181219213
Devuelve:

None

roboticpark_cyberattacks.unused_utils.checkobjective(node)[fuente]

Check the objective of the attack, passed by parameter by Ros ros2 run roboticpark_cyberattacks dosattack –ros-args -p dosobjective:=loquesea It does not work to check the existance of a node because a Node is not able to check the full graph. It only sees a group of nodes in any interaction.

  • double_range_start – range for double values

  • double_range_end – range for double values

  • int_range_start – range for int values

  • int_range_end – range for int values

  • frame_id_string – frame id string

Devuelve:

Formatted msg
